place.name: DUNBOG
place.gazetteerText: Dunbog, par. and quoad sacra par., NW. Fifeshire, 3½ miles E. of Newburgh -- par., 2324 ac., pop. 219; quoad sacra par. (Dunbog and Flisk pars.), pop. 365; contains Dunbog Hill, alt. 707 ft., and D. House, seat of the Earl of Zetland, on site of a preceptory. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
